<div class="container">
  <h1>Create Sari Gallery!</h1>

  <ul>
    <h4>File Upload is coming soon. For now, there are 2 ways to upload your images...</h4>
      <li>Go to imgur.com to upload your image. Imgur will give you a URL, which you can then paste into the Image field below.</li>
      <li>Find an image you like online and paste the URL for it in the Image field in the form below.</li><br>
      <h5>Just in case you're not sure...</h5>
      <li>Story field is the caption that will appear with the image you upload. It can be a story about the image or comment on it, etc. </li>
      <li>Owner is an optional field where you can list if you own it, if it belongs to someone you know, if it was a special gift, etc. or it can be the source of your image (e.g., Google Images). What you list in this field is currently not visible to other users.</li>
  </ul><br><br>
<%= bootstrap_form_for @sari do |f| %>
<% if @sari.errors.any? %>
  <div class="error_messages">
    <h2>Upload is invalid</h2>
    <ul>
      <% for message in @sari.errors.full_messages %>
        <li><%= message %></li>
      <% end %>
    </ul>
  </div>
<% end %>
<div class="field">
  <%= f.text_field :image %>
</div>
<div class="field">
  <%= f.text_field :story %>
</div>
<div class="field">
  <%= f.text_field :owner %>
</div>
<br>
<div class="actions"><%= f.submit class: "btn btn-success" %></div>
<% end %>
<br>
<br>
<button type="button" class="btn btn-default"><%= link_to 'Cancel', user_path(current_user) %></button>
<br>
<br>
<br><button type="button" class="btn btn-default"><%= link_to "See What's Trending Now", saris_path %></button>
<br>
<br>
<div class="container">
<img src="http://ak-hdl.buzzfed.com/static/2013-10/enhanced/webdr05/15/17/enhanced-buzz-8157-1381873037-33.jpg"></div>
</div>





